people.aboutText: Federica Pellegrini (Italian pronunciation: [fedeˈriːka pelleˈɡriːni]; born 5 August 1988) is an Italian swimmer. A native of Mirano, in the province of Venice, she holds the women's 200 m freestyle world records (long course and short course), and won a Gold Medal at the 2008 Beijing Olympics. At the 2009 World Championships in Rome, Pellegrini became the first woman ever to breach the 4 minute barrier in 400 m freestyle with the time 3:59.15.

people.name: Kaimar Saag
people.aboutText: Kaimar Saag (born 5 August 1988) is an Estonian professional footballer who plays as a striker for Estonian Meistriliiga club Levadia and the Estonia national football team.

people.name: Ryan Bertrand
people.aboutText:
Ryan Dominic Bertrand (born 5 August 1989) is an English professional footballer who plays for Southampton as a left back.
Born in Southwark, London, Bertrand began his youth career at Gillingham, before signing for Chelsea in July 2005. Where he graduated from their youth system and was sent on loan to various clubs between 2006 and 2010.

people.name: Mathieu Manset
people.aboutText: Mathieu Manset (born 5 August 1989) is a French footballer who plays as a centre forward.

people.name: Jessica Nigri
people.aboutText: Jessica Nigri (born August 5, 1989) is an American cosplay celebrity, promotional model, YouTuber, voice actress and fan convention interview correspondent.

people.name: Yui Minami
people.aboutText: Saaya Osako (大迫 沙綾, Ōsako Saaya, née Ogura (小倉), born August 5, 1990, in Saitama Prefecture, Japan), better known as Yui Minami (南 結衣, Minami Yui), is a Japanese gravure idol and former child actress who is represented by the talent agency JMO.

people.name: Esteban Gutiérrez
people.aboutText: Esteban Manuel Gutiérrez Gutiérrez (Spanish pronunciation: [esˈteβan maˈnwel ɣuˈtjeres ɣuˈtjeres]; born 5 August 1991), is a Mexican racing driver. From 2011 to 2014, Gutiérrez drove for the Sauber Formula One team, but lost his drive at the end of the 2014 season. He then signed with Ferrari as their test and reserve driver for 2015.

people.name: Konrad Hurrell
people.aboutText: Konileti "Konrad" Hurrell (born 5 August 1991) is a Tongan professional rugby league footballer who currently plays for the New Zealand Warriors in the National Rugby League competition. A Tongan international representative, he has played his entire career to date with the Warriors.

people.name: Andreas Weimann
people.aboutText: Andreas "Andi" Weimann (German pronunciation: [vaɪman]; born 5 August 1991) is an Austrian footballer who plays for English club Derby County and the Austria national team as a forward or winger. He has represented Austria at full international level and also played for Watford during two separate loan spells in 2011. Weimann was signed by Aston Villa as a sixteen-year-old from Rapid Vienna and went on to make over 100 appearances in the Premier League before his transfer to Derby County.

people.name: Chen Ding
people.aboutText: Chen Ding (Chinese: 陈定; born August 5, 1992 in Yunnan, China) is a Chinese racewalker who won a gold medal in the 2012 Summer Olympics in London, United Kingdom.

people.name: Patrick McBrearty
people.aboutText:
Suzuka Ohgo (Japanese: 大後 寿々花, Hepburn: Ōgo Suzuka, born 5 August 1993 in Zama, Kanagawa) is a Japanese actress. She is represented by Alpha Agency.
^ "大後 寿々花 - ALPHA AGENCY｜アルファエージェンシー".

people.name: Suzuka Ohgo
people.aboutText: Patrick "Paddy" McBrearty (born 5 August 1993 in Letterkenny) is an Irish sportsperson. He plays Gaelic football with his local club Chíll Chartha and has been a member of the Donegal senior inter-county team since 2011. A graduate of the Phoenix Elite Academy, he is usually selected in the full-forward line for his county, often flanking Michael Murphy with Colm McFadden.

people.name: Pierre Højbjerg
people.aboutText: Olivia Hastings Holt (born August 5, 1997) is an American teen actress and singer who starred in the Disney Channel Original Series I Didn't Do It. She played the role of Kim on the Disney XD series Kickin' It and starred in the Disney Channel Original Movie Girl vs. Monster.

people.name: Olivia Holt
people.aboutText:
Pierre-Emile Kordt Højbjerg, sometimes as Höjbjerg in Germany, (born 5 August 1995) is a Danish footballer who plays as a midfielder for Schalke 04 on loan from Bayern Munich in the Bundesliga.
With Bayern, he has won a variety of domestic and international tournaments.

people.name: Adam Irigoyen
people.aboutText: Adam Irigoyen (born August 5, 1997) is an American actor, singer, rapper and dancer.

people.name: Mimi Keene
people.aboutText: Mimi Keene (born 5 August 1998) is a British actress, known for her role as Cindy Williams in the BBC soap opera EastEnders. Keene studies at Italia Conti Academy of Theatre Arts  and can be seen on CBBC School for Stars, which shows inside the school and life of some of the pupils.

people.name: Kanon Suzuki
people.aboutText:
Maya Bond (Japanese: マヤ ボンド; born August 5, 2000 in Osaka, Japan) is a former Japanese-born American singer-songwriter and musician. She is the daughter of musician and composer T.W. Bond.
Bond is most notable for her 2004 debut, Pink Drums, Purple Lights, which she is credited for writing all the song lyrics to.

people.name: Maya Bond
people.aboutText:
Kanon Suzuki (Japanese: 鈴木 香音, Hepburn: Suzuki Kanon, born August 5, 1998, Aichi Prefecture) is a J-pop singer. She is a ninth-generation member of the Japanese girl idol group Morning Musume.
^ "Sayumi Michishige's official blog" (in Japanese).
